107struct hb_subset_layout_context_t :
108 hb_dispatch_context_t<hb_subset_layout_context_t, hb_empty_t, HB_DEBUG_SUBSET>
109{
110 const char *get_name () { return "SUBSET_LAYOUT"; }
111 static return_t default_return_value () { return hb_empty_t (); }
112
113 bool visitScript ()
114 {
115 return script_count++ < HB_MAX_SCRIPTS;
116 }
117
118 bool visitLangSys ()
119 {
120 return langsys_count++ < HB_MAX_LANGSYS;
121 }
122
123 bool visitFeatureIndex (int count)
124 {
125 feature_index_count += count;
126 return feature_index_count < HB_MAX_FEATURE_INDICES;
127 }
128
129 bool visitLookupIndex()
130 {
131 lookup_index_count++;
132 return lookup_index_count < HB_MAX_LOOKUP_VISIT_COUNT;
133 }
134
135 hb_subset_context_t *subset_context;
136 const hb_tag_t table_tag;
137 const hb_map_t *lookup_index_map;
138 const hb_hashmap_t<unsigned, hb::unique_ptr<hb_set_t>> *script_langsys_map;
139 const hb_map_t *feature_index_map;
140 const hb_hashmap_t<unsigned, const Feature*> *feature_substitutes_map;
141 hb_hashmap_t<unsigned, hb::shared_ptr<hb_set_t>> *feature_record_cond_idx_map;
142
143 unsigned cur_script_index;
144 unsigned cur_feature_var_record_idx;
145
146 hb_subset_layout_context_t (hb_subset_context_t *c_,
147 hb_tag_t tag_) :
148 subset_context (c_),
149 table_tag (tag_),
150 cur_script_index (0xFFFFu),
151 cur_feature_var_record_idx (0u),
152 script_count (0),
153 langsys_count (0),
154 feature_index_count (0),
155 lookup_index_count (0)
156 {
157 if (tag_ == HB_OT_TAG_GSUB)
158 {
159 lookup_index_map = &c_->plan->gsub_lookups;
160 script_langsys_map = &c_->plan->gsub_langsys;
161 feature_index_map = &c_->plan->gsub_features;
162 feature_substitutes_map = &c_->plan->gsub_feature_substitutes_map;
163 feature_record_cond_idx_map = c_->plan->user_axes_location.is_empty () ? nullptr : &c_->plan->gsub_feature_record_cond_idx_map;
164 }
165 else
166 {
167 lookup_index_map = &c_->plan->gpos_lookups;
168 script_langsys_map = &c_->plan->gpos_langsys;
169 feature_index_map = &c_->plan->gpos_features;
170 feature_substitutes_map = &c_->plan->gpos_feature_substitutes_map;
171 feature_record_cond_idx_map = c_->plan->user_axes_location.is_empty () ? nullptr : &c_->plan->gpos_feature_record_cond_idx_map;
172 }
173 }
174
175 private:
176 unsigned script_count;
177 unsigned langsys_count;
178 unsigned feature_index_count;
179 unsigned lookup_index_count;
180};

214template<typename OutputArray>
215struct subset_offset_array_t
216{
217 subset_offset_array_t (hb_subset_context_t *subset_context_,
218 OutputArray& out_,
219 const void *base_) : subset_context (subset_context_),
220 out (out_), base (base_) {}
221
222 template <typename T>
223 bool operator () (T&& offset)
224 {
225 auto snap = subset_context->serializer->snapshot ();
226 auto *o = out.serialize_append (subset_context->serializer);
227 if (unlikely (!o)) return false;
228 bool ret = o->serialize_subset (subset_context, offset, base);
229 if (!ret)
230 {
231 out.pop ();
232 subset_context->serializer->revert (snap);
233 }
234 return ret;
235 }
236
237 private:
238 hb_subset_context_t *subset_context;
239 OutputArray &out;
240 const void *base;
241};

275/*
276 * Helper to subset an array of offsets. Subsets the thing pointed to by each offset
277 * and discards the offset in the array if the subset operation results in an empty
278 * thing.
279 */
280struct
281{
282 template<typename OutputArray>
283 subset_offset_array_t<OutputArray>
284 operator () (hb_subset_context_t *subset_context, OutputArray& out,
285 const void *base) const
286 { return subset_offset_array_t<OutputArray> (subset_context, out, base); }
287
288 /* Variant with one extra argument passed to serialize_subset */
289 template<typename OutputArray, typename Arg>
290 subset_offset_array_arg_t<OutputArray, Arg>
291 operator () (hb_subset_context_t *subset_context, OutputArray& out,
292 const void *base, Arg &&arg) const
293 { return subset_offset_array_arg_t<OutputArray, Arg> (subset_context, out, base, arg); }
294}
295HB_FUNCOBJ (subset_offset_array);

414struct IndexArray : Array16Of<Index>
415{
416 bool intersects (const hb_map_t *indexes) const
417 { return hb_any (*this, indexes); }
418
419 template <typename Iterator,
420 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iterator))>
421 void serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
422 hb_subset_layout_context_t *l,
423 Iterator it)
424 {
425 if (!it) return;
426 if (unlikely (!c->extend_min ((*this)))) return;
427
428 for (const auto _ : it)
429 {
430 if (!l->visitLookupIndex()) break;
431
432 Index i;
433 i = _;
434 c->copy (src: i);
435 this->len++;
436 }
437 }
438
439 unsigned int get_indexes (unsigned int start_offset,
440 unsigned int *_count /* IN/OUT */,
441 unsigned int *_indexes /* OUT */) const
442 {
443 if (_count)
444 {
445 + this->as_array ().sub_array (start_offset, seg_count: _count)
446 | hb_sink (hb_array (array: _indexes, length: *_count))
447 ;
448 }
449 return this->len;
450 }
451
452 void add_indexes_to (hb_set_t* output /* OUT */) const
453 {
454 output->add_array (arr: as_array ());
455 }
456};

459/* https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/features_pt#size */
460struct FeatureParamsSize
461{
462 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
463 {
464 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
465 if (unlikely (!c->check_struct (this))) return_trace (false);
466
467 /* This subtable has some "history", if you will. Some earlier versions of
468 * Adobe tools calculated the offset of the FeatureParams subtable from the
469 * beginning of the FeatureList table! Now, that is dealt with in the
470 * Feature implementation. But we still need to be able to tell junk from
471 * real data. Note: We don't check that the nameID actually exists.
472 *
473 * Read Roberts wrote on 9/15/06 on opentype-list@indx.co.uk :
474 *
475 * Yes, it is correct that a new version of the AFDKO (version 2.0) will be
476 * coming out soon, and that the makeotf program will build a font with a
477 * 'size' feature that is correct by the specification.
478 *
479 * The specification for this feature tag is in the "OpenType Layout Tag
480 * Registry". You can see a copy of this at:
481 * https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/features_pt#tag-size
482 *
483 * Here is one set of rules to determine if the 'size' feature is built
484 * correctly, or as by the older versions of MakeOTF. You may be able to do
485 * better.
486 *
487 * Assume that the offset to the size feature is according to specification,
488 * and make the following value checks. If it fails, assume the size
489 * feature is calculated as versions of MakeOTF before the AFDKO 2.0 built it.
490 * If this fails, reject the 'size' feature. The older makeOTF's calculated the
491 * offset from the beginning of the FeatureList table, rather than from the
492 * beginning of the 'size' Feature table.
493 *
494 * If "design size" == 0:
495 * fails check
496 *
497 * Else if ("subfamily identifier" == 0 and
498 * "range start" == 0 and
499 * "range end" == 0 and
500 * "range start" == 0 and
501 * "menu name ID" == 0)
502 * passes check: this is the format used when there is a design size
503 * specified, but there is no recommended size range.
504 *
505 * Else if ("design size" < "range start" or
506 * "design size" > "range end" or
507 * "range end" <= "range start" or
508 * "menu name ID" < 256 or
509 * "menu name ID" > 32767 or
510 * menu name ID is not a name ID which is actually in the name table)
511 * fails test
512 * Else
513 * passes test.
514 */
515
516 if (!designSize)
517 return_trace (false);
518 else if (subfamilyID == 0 &&
519 subfamilyNameID == 0 &&
520 rangeStart == 0 &&
521 rangeEnd == 0)
522 return_trace (true);
523 else if (designSize < rangeStart ||
524 designSize > rangeEnd ||
525 subfamilyNameID < 256 ||
526 subfamilyNameID > 32767)
527 return_trace (false);
528 else
529 return_trace (true);
530 }
531
532 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c) const
533 {
534 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
535 return_trace ((bool) c->serializer->embed (*this));
536 }
537
538 HBUINT16 designSize; /* Represents the design size in 720/inch
539 * units (decipoints). The design size entry
540 * must be non-zero. When there is a design
541 * size but no recommended size range, the
542 * rest of the array will consist of zeros. */
543 HBUINT16 subfamilyID; /* Has no independent meaning, but serves
544 * as an identifier that associates fonts
545 * in a subfamily. All fonts which share a
546 * Preferred or Font Family name and which
547 * differ only by size range shall have the
548 * same subfamily value, and no fonts which
549 * differ in weight or style shall have the
550 * same subfamily value. If this value is
551 * zero, the remaining fields in the array
552 * will be ignored. */
553 NameID subfamilyNameID;/* If the preceding value is non-zero, this
554 * value must be set in the range 256 - 32767
555 * (inclusive). It records the value of a
556 * field in the name table, which must
557 * contain English-language strings encoded
558 * in Windows Unicode and Macintosh Roman,
559 * and may contain additional strings
560 * localized to other scripts and languages.
561 * Each of these strings is the name an
562 * application should use, in combination
563 * with the family name, to represent the
564 * subfamily in a menu. Applications will
565 * choose the appropriate version based on
566 * their selection criteria. */
567 HBUINT16 rangeStart; /* Large end of the recommended usage range
568 * (inclusive), stored in 720/inch units
569 * (decipoints). */
570 HBUINT16 rangeEnd; /* Small end of the recommended usage range
571 (exclusive), stored in 720/inch units
572 * (decipoints). */
573 public:
574 DEFINE_SIZE_STATIC (10);
575};

577/* https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/features_pt#ssxx */
578struct FeatureParamsStylisticSet
579{
580 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
581 {
582 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
583 /* Right now minorVersion is at zero. Which means, any table supports
584 * the uiNameID field. */
585 return_trace (c->check_struct (this));
586 }
587
588 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c) const
589 {
590 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
591 return_trace ((bool) c->serializer->embed (*this));
592 }
593
594 HBUINT16 version; /* (set to 0): This corresponds to a “minor”
595 * version number. Additional data may be
596 * added to the end of this Feature Parameters
597 * table in the future. */
598
599 NameID uiNameID; /* The 'name' table name ID that specifies a
600 * string (or strings, for multiple languages)
601 * for a user-interface label for this
602 * feature. The values of uiLabelNameId and
603 * sampleTextNameId are expected to be in the
604 * font-specific name ID range (256-32767),
605 * though that is not a requirement in this
606 * Feature Parameters specification. The
607 * user-interface label for the feature can
608 * be provided in multiple languages. An
609 * English string should be included as a
610 * fallback. The string should be kept to a
611 * minimal length to fit comfortably with
612 * different application interfaces. */
613 public:
614 DEFINE_SIZE_STATIC (4);
615};

617/* https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/features_ae#cv01-cv99 */
618struct FeatureParamsCharacterVariants
619{
620 unsigned
621 get_characters (unsigned start_offset, unsigned *char_count, hb_codepoint_t *chars) const
622 {
623 if (char_count)
624 {
625 + characters.as_array ().sub_array (start_offset, seg_count: char_count)
626 | hb_sink (hb_array (array: chars, length: *char_count))
627 ;
628 }
629 return characters.len;
630 }
631
632 unsigned get_size () const
633 { return min_size + characters.len * HBUINT24::static_size; }
634
635 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c) const
636 {
637 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
638 return_trace ((bool) c->serializer->embed (*this));
639 }
640
641 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
642 {
643 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
644 return_trace (c->check_struct (this) &&
645 characters.sanitize (c));
646 }
647
648 HBUINT16 format; /* Format number is set to 0. */
649 NameID featUILableNameID; /* The ‘name’ table name ID that
650 * specifies a string (or strings,
651 * for multiple languages) for a
652 * user-interface label for this
653 * feature. (May be NULL.) */
654 NameID featUITooltipTextNameID;/* The ‘name’ table name ID that
655 * specifies a string (or strings,
656 * for multiple languages) that an
657 * application can use for tooltip
658 * text for this feature. (May be
659 * nullptr.) */
660 NameID sampleTextNameID; /* The ‘name’ table name ID that
661 * specifies sample text that
662 * illustrates the effect of this
663 * feature. (May be NULL.) */
664 HBUINT16 numNamedParameters; /* Number of named parameters. (May
665 * be zero.) */
666 NameID firstParamUILabelNameID;/* The first ‘name’ table name ID
667 * used to specify strings for
668 * user-interface labels for the
669 * feature parameters. (Must be zero
670 * if numParameters is zero.) */
671 Array16Of<HBUINT24>
672 characters; /* Array of the Unicode Scalar Value
673 * of the characters for which this
674 * feature provides glyph variants.
675 * (May be zero.) */
676 public:
677 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY (14, characters);
678};
679
680struct FeatureParams
681{
682 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c, hb_tag_t tag) const
683 {
684#ifdef HB_NO_LAYOUT_FEATURE_PARAMS
685 return true;
686#endif
687 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
688 if (tag == HB_TAG ('s','i','z','e'))
689 return_trace (u.size.sanitize (c));
690 if ((tag & 0xFFFF0000u) == HB_TAG ('s','s','\0','\0')) /* ssXX */
691 return_trace (u.stylisticSet.sanitize (c));
692 if ((tag & 0xFFFF0000u) == HB_TAG ('c','v','\0','\0')) /* cvXX */
693 return_trace (u.characterVariants.sanitize (c));
694 return_trace (true);
695 }

697 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c, const Tag* tag) const
698 {
699 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
700 if (!tag) return_trace (false);
701 if (*tag == HB_TAG ('s','i','z','e'))
702 return_trace (u.size.subset (c));
703 if ((*tag & 0xFFFF0000u) == HB_TAG ('s','s','\0','\0')) /* ssXX */
704 return_trace (u.stylisticSet.subset (c));
705 if ((*tag & 0xFFFF0000u) == HB_TAG ('c','v','\0','\0')) /* cvXX */
706 return_trace (u.characterVariants.subset (c));
707 return_trace (false);
708 }
709
710#ifndef HB_NO_LAYOUT_FEATURE_PARAMS
711 const FeatureParamsSize& get_size_params (hb_tag_t tag) const
712 {
713 if (tag == HB_TAG ('s','i','z','e'))
714 return u.size;
715 return Null (FeatureParamsSize);
716 }
717 const FeatureParamsStylisticSet& get_stylistic_set_params (hb_tag_t tag) const
718 {
719 if ((tag & 0xFFFF0000u) == HB_TAG ('s','s','\0','\0')) /* ssXX */
720 return u.stylisticSet;
721 return Null (FeatureParamsStylisticSet);
722 }
723 const FeatureParamsCharacterVariants& get_character_variants_params (hb_tag_t tag) const
724 {
725 if ((tag & 0xFFFF0000u) == HB_TAG ('c','v','\0','\0')) /* cvXX */
726 return u.characterVariants;
727 return Null (FeatureParamsCharacterVariants);
728 }
729#endif

765 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c,
766 hb_subset_layout_context_t *l,
767 const Tag *tag = nullptr) const
768 {
769 TRACE_SUBSET (this);

771 if (unlikely (!out || !c->serializer->extend_min (out))) return_trace (false);
772
773 out->featureParams.serialize_subset (c, src: featureParams, src_base: this, ds&: tag);
774
775 auto it =
776 + hb_iter (lookupIndex)
777 | hb_filter (l->lookup_index_map)
778 | hb_map (l->lookup_index_map)
779 ;
780

783 // so always retain it.

786
787 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c,
788 const Record_sanitize_closure_t *closure = nullptr) const
789 {
790 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
791 if (unlikely (!(c->check_struct (this) && lookupIndex.sanitize (c))))
792 return_trace (false);
793
794 /* Some earlier versions of Adobe tools calculated the offset of the
795 * FeatureParams subtable from the beginning of the FeatureList table!
796 *
797 * If sanitizing "failed" for the FeatureParams subtable, try it with the
798 * alternative location. We would know sanitize "failed" if old value
799 * of the offset was non-zero, but it's zeroed now.
800 *
801 * Only do this for the 'size' feature, since at the time of the faulty
802 * Adobe tools, only the 'size' feature had FeatureParams defined.
803 */
804
805 if (likely (featureParams.is_null ()))
806 return_trace (true);
807
808 unsigned int orig_offset = featureParams;
809 if (unlikely (!featureParams.sanitize (c, this, closure ? closure->tag : HB_TAG_NONE)))
810 return_trace (false);
811
812 if (featureParams == 0 && closure &&
813 closure->tag == HB_TAG ('s','i','z','e') &&
814 closure->list_base && closure->list_base < this)
815 {
816 unsigned int new_offset_int = orig_offset -
817 (((char *) this) - ((char *) closure->list_base));
818
819 Offset16To<FeatureParams> new_offset;
820 /* Check that it would not overflow. */
821 new_offset = new_offset_int;
822 if (new_offset == new_offset_int &&
823 c->try_set (obj: &featureParams, v: new_offset_int) &&
824 !featureParams.sanitize (c, base: this, ds: closure ? closure->tag : HB_TAG_NONE))
825 return_trace (false);
826 }
827
828 return_trace (true);
829 }
830
831 Offset16To<FeatureParams>
832 featureParams; /* Offset to Feature Parameters table (if one
833 * has been defined for the feature), relative
834 * to the beginning of the Feature Table; = Null
835 * if not required */
836 IndexArray lookupIndex; /* Array of LookupList indices */
837 public:
838 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY_SIZED (4, lookupIndex);
839};

993
994 bool compare (const LangSys& o, const hb_map_t *feature_index_map) const
995 {
996 if (reqFeatureIndex != o.reqFeatureIndex)
997 return false;
998
999 auto iter =
1000 + hb_iter (featureIndex)
1001 | hb_filter (feature_index_map)
1002 | hb_map (feature_index_map)
1003 ;
1004
1005 auto o_iter =
1006 + hb_iter (o.featureIndex)
1007 | hb_filter (feature_index_map)
1008 | hb_map (feature_index_map)
1009 ;
1010
1011 for (; iter && o_iter; iter++, o_iter++)
1012 {
1013 unsigned a = *iter;
1014 unsigned b = *o_iter;
1015 if (a != b) return false;
1016 }
1017
1018 if (iter || o_iter) return false;
1019
1020 return true;
1021 }

1024 {
1025 if (!has_required_feature () && !get_feature_count ()) return;
1026 if (has_required_feature () &&
1027 c->duplicate_feature_map->has (key: reqFeatureIndex))
1028 c->new_feature_indexes->add (g: get_required_feature_index ());
1029
1030 + hb_iter (featureIndex)
1031 | hb_filter (c->duplicate_feature_map)
1032 | hb_sink (c->new_feature_indexes)
1033 ;
1034 }

1051 + hb_iter (featureIndex)

1100 void prune_langsys (hb_prune_langsys_context_t *c,
1101 unsigned script_index) const
1102 {
1103 if (!has_default_lang_sys () && !get_lang_sys_count ()) return;
1104 if (!c->visitScript ()) return;
1105
1106 if (!c->script_langsys_map->has (key: script_index))
1107 {
1108 if (unlikely (!c->script_langsys_map->set (script_index, hb::unique_ptr<hb_set_t> {hb_set_create ()})))
1109 return;
1110 }
1111
1112 if (has_default_lang_sys ())
1113 {
1114 //only collect features from non-redundant langsys
1115 const LangSys& d = get_default_lang_sys ();
1116 if (c->visitLangsys (feature_count: d.get_feature_count ())) {
1117 d.collect_features (c);
1118 }
1119
1120 for (auto _ : + hb_enumerate (langSys))
1121 {
1122 const LangSys& l = this+_.second.offset;
1123 if (!c->visitLangsys (feature_count: l.get_feature_count ())) continue;
1124 if (l.compare (o: d, feature_index_map: c->duplicate_feature_map)) continue;
1125
1126 l.collect_features (c);
1127 c->script_langsys_map->get (key: script_index)->add (g: _.first);
1128 }
1129 }
1130 else
1131 {
1132 for (auto _ : + hb_enumerate (langSys))
1133 {
1134 const LangSys& l = this+_.second.offset;
1135 if (!c->visitLangsys (feature_count: l.get_feature_count ())) continue;
1136 l.collect_features (c);
1137 c->script_langsys_map->get (key: script_index)->add (g: _.first);
1138 }
1139 }
1140 }

1142 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c,
1143 hb_subset_layout_context_t *l,
1144 const Tag *tag) const
1145 {
1146 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
1147 if (!l->visitScript ()) return_trace (false);
1148 if (tag && !c->plan->layout_scripts.has (k: *tag))
1149 return false;
1150
1151 auto *out = c->serializer->start_embed (obj: *this);
1152 if (unlikely (!out || !c->serializer->extend_min (out))) return_trace (false);
1153
1154 bool defaultLang = false;
1155 if (has_default_lang_sys ())
1156 {
1157 c->serializer->push ();
1158 const LangSys& ls = this+defaultLangSys;
1159 bool ret = ls.subset (c, l);
1160 if (!ret && tag && *tag != HB_TAG ('D', 'F', 'L', 'T'))
1161 {
1162 c->serializer->pop_discard ();
1163 out->defaultLangSys = 0;
1164 }
1165 else
1166 {
1167 c->serializer->add_link (ofs&: out->defaultLangSys, objidx: c->serializer->pop_pack ());
1168 defaultLang = true;
1169 }
1170 }
1171
1172 const hb_set_t *active_langsys = l->script_langsys_map->get (key: l->cur_script_index);
1173 if (active_langsys)
1174 {
1175 + hb_enumerate (langSys)
1176 | hb_filter (active_langsys, hb_first)
1177 | hb_map (hb_second)
1178 | hb_filter ([=] (const Record<LangSys>& record) {return l->visitLangSys (); })
1179 | hb_apply (subset_record_array (l, &(out->langSys), this))
1180 ;
1181 }
1182
1183 return_trace (bool (out->langSys.len) || defaultLang || l->table_tag == HB_OT_TAG_GSUB);
1184 }

1188 {
1189 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
1190 return_trace (defaultLangSys.sanitize (c, this) && langSys.sanitize (c, this));
1191 }

1251struct Lookup
1252{
1253 unsigned int get_subtable_count () const { return subTable.len; }
1254
1255 template <typename TSubTable>
1256 const Array16OfOffset16To<TSubTable>& get_subtables () const
1257 { return reinterpret_cast<const Array16OfOffset16To<TSubTable> &> (subTable); }
1258 template <typename TSubTable>
1259 Array16OfOffset16To<TSubTable>& get_subtables ()
1260 { return reinterpret_cast<Array16OfOffset16To<TSubTable> &> (subTable); }
1261
1262 template <typename TSubTable>
1263 const TSubTable& get_subtable (unsigned int i) const
1264 { return this+get_subtables<TSubTable> ()[i]; }
1265 template <typename TSubTable>
1266 TSubTable& get_subtable (unsigned int i)
1267 { return this+get_subtables<TSubTable> ()[i]; }
1268
1269 unsigned int get_size () const
1270 {
1271 const HBUINT16 &markFilteringSet = StructAfter<const HBUINT16> (X: subTable);
1272 if (lookupFlag & LookupFlag::UseMarkFilteringSet)
1273 return (const char *) &StructAfter<const char> (X: markFilteringSet) - (const char *) this;
1274 return (const char *) &markFilteringSet - (const char *) this;
1275 }
1276
1277 unsigned int get_type () const { return lookupType; }
1278
1279 /* lookup_props is a 32-bit integer where the lower 16-bit is LookupFlag and
1280 * higher 16-bit is mark-filtering-set if the lookup uses one.
1281 * Not to be confused with glyph_props which is very similar. */
1282 uint32_t get_props () const
1283 {
1284 unsigned int flag = lookupFlag;
1285 if (unlikely (flag & LookupFlag::UseMarkFilteringSet))
1286 {
1287 const HBUINT16 &markFilteringSet = StructAfter<HBUINT16> (X: subTable);
1288 flag += (markFilteringSet << 16);
1289 }
1290 return flag;
1291 }
1292
1293 template <typename TSubTable, typename context_t, typename ...Ts>
1294 typename context_t::return_t dispatch (context_t *c, Ts&&... ds) const
1295 {
1296 unsigned int lookup_type = get_type ();
1297 TRACE_DISPATCH (this, lookup_type);
1298 unsigned int count = get_subtable_count ();
1299 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
1300 typename context_t::return_t r = get_subtable<TSubTable> (i).dispatch (c, lookup_type, std::forward<Ts> (ds)...);
1301 if (c->stop_sublookup_iteration (r))
1302 return_trace (r);
1303 }
1304 return_trace (c->default_return_value ());
1305 }
1306
1307 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
1308 unsigned int lookup_type,
1309 uint32_t lookup_props,
1310 unsigned int num_subtables)
1311 {
1312 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
1313 if (unlikely (!c->extend_min (this))) return_trace (false);
1314 lookupType = lookup_type;
1315 lookupFlag = lookup_props & 0xFFFFu;
1316 if (unlikely (!subTable.serialize (c, num_subtables))) return_trace (false);
1317 if (lookupFlag & LookupFlag::UseMarkFilteringSet)
1318 {
1319 if (unlikely (!c->extend (this))) return_trace (false);
1320 HBUINT16 &markFilteringSet = StructAfter<HBUINT16> (X&: subTable);
1321 markFilteringSet = lookup_props >> 16;
1322 }
1323 return_trace (true);
1324 }
1325
1326 template <typename TSubTable>
1327 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c) const
1328 {
1329 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
1330 auto *out = c->serializer->start_embed (obj: *this);
1331 if (unlikely (!out || !c->serializer->extend_min (out))) return_trace (false);
1332 out->lookupType = lookupType;
1333 out->lookupFlag = lookupFlag;
1334
1335 const hb_set_t *glyphset = c->plan->glyphset_gsub ();
1336 unsigned int lookup_type = get_type ();
1337 + hb_iter (get_subtables <TSubTable> ())
1338 | hb_filter ([this, glyphset, lookup_type] (const Offset16To<TSubTable> &_) { return (this+_).intersects (glyphset, lookup_type); })
1339 | hb_apply (subset_offset_array (c, out->get_subtables<TSubTable> (), this, lookup_type))
1340 ;
1341
1342 if (lookupFlag & LookupFlag::UseMarkFilteringSet)
1343 {
1344 if (unlikely (!c->serializer->extend (out))) return_trace (false);
1345 const HBUINT16 &markFilteringSet = StructAfter<HBUINT16> (X: subTable);
1346 HBUINT16 &outMarkFilteringSet = StructAfter<HBUINT16> (X&: out->subTable);
1347 outMarkFilteringSet = markFilteringSet;
1348 }
1349
1350 // Always keep the lookup even if it's empty. The rest of layout subsetting depends on lookup
1351 // indices being consistent with those computed during planning. So if an empty lookup is
1352 // discarded during the subset phase it will invalidate all subsequent lookup indices.
1353 // Generally we shouldn't end up with an empty lookup as we pre-prune them during the planning
1354 // phase, but it can happen in rare cases such as when during closure subtable is considered
1355 // degenerate (see: https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/3853)
1356 return_trace (true);
1357 }
1358
1359 template <typename TSubTable>
1360 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
1361 {
1362 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
1363 if (!(c->check_struct (obj: this) && subTable.sanitize (c))) return_trace (false);
1364
1365 unsigned subtables = get_subtable_count ();
1366 if (unlikely (!c->visit_subtables (subtables))) return_trace (false);
1367
1368 if (lookupFlag & LookupFlag::UseMarkFilteringSet)
1369 {
1370 const HBUINT16 &markFilteringSet = StructAfter<HBUINT16> (X: subTable);
1371 if (!markFilteringSet.sanitize (c)) return_trace (false);
1372 }
1373
1374 if (unlikely (!get_subtables<TSubTable> ().sanitize (c, this, get_type ())))
1375 return_trace (false);
1376
1377 if (unlikely (get_type () == TSubTable::Extension && !c->get_edit_count ()))
1378 {
1379 /* The spec says all subtables of an Extension lookup should
1380 * have the same type, which shall not be the Extension type
1381 * itself (but we already checked for that).
1382 * This is specially important if one has a reverse type!
1383 *
1384 * We only do this if sanitizer edit_count is zero. Otherwise,
1385 * some of the subtables might have become insane after they
1386 * were sanity-checked by the edits of subsequent subtables.
1387 * https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=960331
1388 */
1389 unsigned int type = get_subtable<TSubTable> (0).u.extension.get_type ();
1390 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < subtables; i++)
1391 if (get_subtable<TSubTable> (i).u.extension.get_type () != type)
1392 return_trace (false);
1393 }
1394 return_trace (true);
1395 }
1396
1397 protected:
1398 HBUINT16 lookupType; /* Different enumerations for GSUB and GPOS */
1399 HBUINT16 lookupFlag; /* Lookup qualifiers */
1400 Array16Of<Offset16>
1401 subTable; /* Array of SubTables */
1402/*HBUINT16 markFilteringSetX[HB_VAR_ARRAY];*//* Index (base 0) into GDEF mark glyph sets
1403 * structure. This field is only present if bit
1404 * UseMarkFilteringSet of lookup flags is set. */
1405 public:
1406 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY (6, subTable);
1407};

1409template <typename Types>
1410using LookupList = List16OfOffsetTo<Lookup, typename Types::HBUINT>;
1411
1412template <typename TLookup, typename OffsetType>
1413struct LookupOffsetList : List16OfOffsetTo<TLookup, OffsetType>
1414{
1415 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c,
1416 hb_subset_layout_context_t *l) const
1417 {
1418 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
1419 auto *out = c->serializer->start_embed (this);
1420 if (unlikely (!out || !c->serializer->extend_min (out))) return_trace (false);
1421
1422 + hb_enumerate (*this)
1423 | hb_filter (l->lookup_index_map, hb_first)
1424 | hb_map (hb_second)
1425 | hb_apply (subset_offset_array (c, *out, this))
1426 ;
1427 return_trace (true);
1428 }
1429
1430 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
1431 {
1432 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
1433 return_trace (List16OfOffset16To<TLookup>::sanitize (c, this));
1434 }
1435};

1439 * Coverage Table
1440 */
1441
1442
1443static bool ClassDef_remap_and_serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
1444 const hb_set_t &klasses,
1445 bool use_class_zero,
1446 hb_sorted_vector_t<hb_pair_t<hb_codepoint_t, hb_codepoint_t>> &glyph_and_klass, /* IN/OUT */
1447 hb_map_t *klass_map /*IN/OUT*/)
1448{
1449 if (!klass_map)
1450 return ClassDef_serialize (c, it: glyph_and_klass.iter ());
1451
1452 /* any glyph not assigned a class value falls into Class zero (0),
1453 * if any glyph assigned to class 0, remapping must start with 0->0*/
1454 if (!use_class_zero)
1455 klass_map->set (key: 0, value: 0);
1456
1457 unsigned idx = klass_map->has (key: 0) ? 1 : 0;
1458 for (const unsigned k: klasses)
1459 {
1460 if (klass_map->has (key: k)) continue;
1461 klass_map->set (key: k, value&: idx);
1462 idx++;
1463 }
1464
1465
1466 for (unsigned i = 0; i < glyph_and_klass.length; i++)
1467 {
1468 hb_codepoint_t klass = glyph_and_klass[i].second;
1469 glyph_and_klass[i].second = klass_map->get (key: klass);
1470 }
1471
1472 c->propagate_error (o1&: glyph_and_klass, os: klasses);
1473 return ClassDef_serialize (c, it: glyph_and_klass.iter ());
1474}

1480template <typename Types>
1481struct ClassDefFormat1_3
1482{
1483 friend struct ClassDef;
1484
1485 private:

1487 {

1489 }

1495
1496 template<typename Iterator,
1497 hb_requires (hb_is_sorted_source_of (Iterator, hb_codepoint_t))>
1498 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
1499 Iterator it)
1500 {
1501 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
1502 if (unlikely (!c->extend_min (this))) return_trace (false);
1503
1504 if (unlikely (!it))
1505 {
1506 classFormat = 1;
1507 startGlyph = 0;
1508 classValue.len = 0;
1509 return_trace (true);
1510 }
1511
1512 hb_codepoint_t glyph_min = (*it).first;
1513 hb_codepoint_t glyph_max = + it
1514 | hb_map (hb_first)
1515 | hb_reduce (hb_max, 0u);
1516 unsigned glyph_count = glyph_max - glyph_min + 1;
1517
1518 startGlyph = glyph_min;
1519 if (unlikely (!classValue.serialize (c, glyph_count))) return_trace (false);
1520 for (const hb_pair_t<hb_codepoint_t, uint32_t> gid_klass_pair : + it)
1521 {
1522 unsigned idx = gid_klass_pair.first - glyph_min;
1523 classValue[idx] = gid_klass_pair.second;
1524 }
1525 return_trace (true);
1526 }
1527
1528 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c,
1529 hb_map_t *klass_map = nullptr /*OUT*/,
1530 bool keep_empty_table = true,
1531 bool use_class_zero = true,
1532 const Coverage* glyph_filter = nullptr) const
1533 {
1534 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
1535 const hb_map_t &glyph_map = c->plan->glyph_map_gsub;
1536
1537 hb_sorted_vector_t<hb_pair_t<hb_codepoint_t, hb_codepoint_t>> glyph_and_klass;
1538 hb_set_t orig_klasses;
1539
1540 hb_codepoint_t start = startGlyph;
1541 hb_codepoint_t end = start + classValue.len;
1542
1543 for (const hb_codepoint_t gid : + hb_range (start, end))
1544 {
1545 hb_codepoint_t new_gid = glyph_map[gid];
1546 if (new_gid == HB_MAP_VALUE_INVALID) continue;
1547 if (glyph_filter && !glyph_filter->has(k: gid)) continue;
1548
1549 unsigned klass = classValue[gid - start];
1550 if (!klass) continue;
1551
1552 glyph_and_klass.push (v: hb_pair (a&: new_gid, b&: klass));
1553 orig_klasses.add (g: klass);
1554 }
1555
1556 unsigned glyph_count = glyph_filter
1557 ? hb_len (hb_iter (glyph_map.keys()) | hb_filter (glyph_filter))
1558 : glyph_map.get_population ();
1559 use_class_zero = use_class_zero && glyph_count <= glyph_and_klass.length;
1560 if (!ClassDef_remap_and_serialize (c: c->serializer,
1561 klasses: orig_klasses,
1562 use_class_zero,
1563 glyph_and_klass,
1564 klass_map))
1565 return_trace (false);
1566 return_trace (keep_empty_table || (bool) glyph_and_klass);
1567 }

1570 {
1571 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
1572 return_trace (c->check_struct (this) && classValue.sanitize (c));
1573 }

1577 template <typename set_t>
1578 bool collect_coverage (set_t *glyphs) const
1579 {
1580 unsigned int start = 0;
1581 unsigned int count = classValue.len;
1582 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
1583 {
1584 if (classValue[i])
1585 continue;
1586
1587 if (start != i)
1588 if (unlikely (!glyphs->add_range (startGlyph + start, startGlyph + i)))
1589 return false;
1590
1591 start = i + 1;
1592 }
1593 if (start != count)
1594 if (unlikely (!glyphs->add_range (startGlyph + start, startGlyph + count)))
1595 return false;
1596
1597 return true;
1598 }

1613 for (hb_codepoint_t iter = startGlyph - 1;
1614 glyphs->next (codepoint: &iter) && iter < end;)
1615 if (classValue[iter - start]) return true;
1616 return false;
1617 }
1618 bool intersects_class (const hb_set_t *glyphs, uint16_t klass) const
1619 {
1620 unsigned int count = classValue.len;
1621 if (klass == 0)
1622 {
1623 /* Match if there's any glyph that is not listed! */
1624 hb_codepoint_t g = HB_SET_VALUE_INVALID;
1625 if (!glyphs->next (codepoint: &g)) return false;
1626 if (g < startGlyph) return true;
1627 g = startGlyph + count - 1;
1628 if (glyphs->next (codepoint: &g)) return true;
1629 /* Fall through. */
1630 }
1631 /* TODO Speed up, using set overlap first? */
1632 /* TODO(iter) Rewrite as dagger. */
1633 const HBUINT16 *arr = classValue.arrayZ;
1634 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
1635 if (arr[i] == klass && glyphs->has (k: startGlyph + i))
1636 return true;
1637 return false;
1638 }

1641 {

1643 if (klass == 0)
1644 {
1645 unsigned start_glyph = startGlyph;
1646 for (uint32_t g = HB_SET_VALUE_INVALID;
1647 glyphs->next (codepoint: &g) && g < start_glyph;)
1648 intersect_glyphs->add (g);
1649
1650 for (uint32_t g = startGlyph + count - 1;
1651 glyphs-> next (codepoint: &g);)
1652 intersect_glyphs->add (g);
1653
1654 return;
1655 }
1656
1657 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; i++)
1658 if (classValue[i] == klass && glyphs->has (k: startGlyph + i))
1659 intersect_glyphs->add (g: startGlyph + i);
1660
1661#if 0
1662 /* The following implementation is faster asymptotically, but slower
1663 * in practice. */
1664 unsigned start_glyph = startGlyph;
1665 unsigned end_glyph = start_glyph + count;
1666 for (unsigned g = startGlyph - 1;
1667 glyphs->next (&g) && g < end_glyph;)
1668 if (classValue.arrayZ[g - start_glyph] == klass)

1670#endif

1674 {
1675 if (glyphs->is_empty ()) return;

1677 if (glyphs->get_min () < startGlyph ||
1678 glyphs->get_max () > end_glyph)
1679 intersect_classes->add (g: 0);
1680
1681 for (const auto& _ : + hb_enumerate (classValue))
1682 {
1683 hb_codepoint_t g = startGlyph + _.first;
1684 if (glyphs->has (k: g))
1685 intersect_classes->add (g: _.second);
1686 }
1687 }

1695 public:

1697};

1699template <typename Types>
1700struct ClassDefFormat2_4
1701{

1703

1706 {
1707 return rangeRecord.bsearch (glyph_id).value;
1708 }
1709
1710 unsigned get_population () const
1711 {
1712 typename Types::large_int ret = 0;
1713 for (const auto &r : rangeRecord)
1714 ret += r.get_population ();
1715 return ret > UINT_MAX ? UINT_MAX : (unsigned) ret;
1716 }
1717
1718 template<typename Iterator,
1719 hb_requires (hb_is_sorted_source_of (Iterator, hb_codepoint_t))>
1720 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
1721 Iterator it)
1722 {
1723 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
1724 if (unlikely (!c->extend_min (this))) return_trace (false);
1725
1726 if (unlikely (!it))
1727 {
1728 classFormat = 2;
1729 rangeRecord.len = 0;
1730 return_trace (true);
1731 }
1732
1733 unsigned num_ranges = 1;
1734 hb_codepoint_t prev_gid = (*it).first;
1735 unsigned prev_klass = (*it).second;
1736
1737 RangeRecord<Types> range_rec;
1738 range_rec.first = prev_gid;
1739 range_rec.last = prev_gid;
1740 range_rec.value = prev_klass;
1741
1742 auto *record = c->copy (range_rec);
1743 if (unlikely (!record)) return_trace (false);
1744
1745 for (const auto gid_klass_pair : + (++it))
1746 {
1747 hb_codepoint_t cur_gid = gid_klass_pair.first;
1748 unsigned cur_klass = gid_klass_pair.second;
1749
1750 if (cur_gid != prev_gid + 1 ||
1751 cur_klass != prev_klass)
1752 {
1753 if (unlikely (!record)) break;
1754 record->last = prev_gid;
1755 num_ranges++;
1756
1757 range_rec.first = cur_gid;
1758 range_rec.last = cur_gid;
1759 range_rec.value = cur_klass;
1760
1761 record = c->copy (range_rec);
1762 }
1763
1764 prev_klass = cur_klass;
1765 prev_gid = cur_gid;
1766 }
1767
1768 if (likely (record)) record->last = prev_gid;
1769 rangeRecord.len = num_ranges;
1770 return_trace (true);
1771 }

1956 for (auto &range : rangeRecord)
1957 {

2025
2026 auto it = + it_with_class_zero | hb_filter (hb_second);

2030 if (likely (it))

2033 glyph_max = glyph_min;
2034
2035 unsigned num_glyphs = 0;
2036 unsigned num_ranges = 1;

2043 unsigned cur_klass = gid_klass_pair.second;
2044 num_glyphs++;
2045 if (cur_gid == glyph_min) continue;
2046 if (cur_gid > glyph_max) glyph_max = cur_gid;
2047 if (cur_gid != prev_gid + 1 ||
2048 cur_klass != prev_klass)
2049 num_ranges++;

2052 prev_klass = cur_klass;

2233{

2235 {
2236 int start = startCoord.to_int (), peak = peakCoord.to_int (), end = endCoord.to_int ();
2237
2238 /* TODO Move these to sanitize(). */
2239 if (unlikely (start > peak || peak > end))
2240 return 1.;
2241 if (unlikely (start < 0 && end > 0 && peak != 0))
2242 return 1.;
2243
2244 if (peak == 0 || coord == peak)
2245 return 1.;
2246
2247 if (coord <= start || end <= coord)
2248 return 0.;

2250 /* Interpolate */

2252 return float (coord - start) / (peak - start);
2253 else

2276{

2279 float evaluate (unsigned int region_index,
2280 const int *coords, unsigned int coord_len,
2281 cache_t *cache = nullptr) const
2282 {
2283 if (unlikely (region_index >= regionCount))
2284 return 0.;
2285
2286 float *cached_value = nullptr;
2287 if (cache)
2288 {
2289 cached_value = &(cache[region_index]);
2290 if (likely (*cached_value != REGION_CACHE_ITEM_CACHE_INVALID))
2291 return *cached_value;
2292 }

2294 const VarRegionAxis *axes = axesZ.arrayZ + (region_index * axisCount);

2298 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
2299 {
2300 int coord = i < coord_len ? coords[i] : 0;
2301 float factor = axes[i].evaluate (coord);
2302 if (factor == 0.f)

2305 *cached_value = 0.;
2306 return 0.;

2308 v *= factor;
2309 }

2445 /* Optimize word count */
2446 unsigned ri_count = src->regionIndices.len;
2447 enum delta_size_t { kZero=0, kNonWord, kWord };

2450 delta_sz.resize (size_: ri_count);

2461 if (src_long_words)

2472 break;

2483

2485 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < inner_map.get_next_value (); i++)

2488 int32_t delta = src->get_item_delta_fast (item: old, region: r, delta_bytes: src_delta_bytes, row_size: src_row_size);
2489 if (delta < min_threshold || max_threshold < delta)

2493 break;

2495 else if (delta != 0)

2498 if (short_circuit)
2499 break;
2500 }
2501 }
2502 }

2516

3405 unsigned int get_size () const
3406 {
3407 unsigned int f = deltaFormat;
3408 if (unlikely (f < 1 || f > 3 || startSize > endSize)) return 3 * HBUINT16::static_size;
3409 return HBUINT16::static_size * (4 + ((endSize - startSize) >> (4 - f)));

3425
3426 int get_delta (unsigned int ppem, int scale) const
3427 {
3428 if (!ppem) return 0;
3429
3430 int pixels = get_delta_pixels (ppem_size: ppem);
3431
3432 if (!pixels) return 0;
3433
3434 return (int) (pixels * (int64_t) scale / ppem);
3435 }
3436 int get_delta_pixels (unsigned int ppem_size) const
3437 {
3438 unsigned int f = deltaFormat;
3439 if (unlikely (f < 1 || f > 3))
3440 return 0;
3441
3442 if (ppem_size < startSize || ppem_size > endSize)
3443 return 0;
3444
3445 unsigned int s = ppem_size - startSize;
3446
3447 unsigned int byte = deltaValueZ[s >> (4 - f)];
3448 unsigned int bits = (byte >> (16 - (((s & ((1 << (4 - f)) - 1)) + 1) << f)));
3449 unsigned int mask = (0xFFFFu >> (16 - (1 << f)));
3450
3451 int delta = bits & mask;
3452
3453 if ((unsigned int) delta >= ((mask + 1) >> 1))
3454 delta -= mask + 1;
3455
3456 return delta;
3457 }
3458
3459 protected:
3460 HBUINT16 startSize; /* Smallest size to correct--in ppem */
3461 HBUINT16 endSize; /* Largest size to correct--in ppem */
3462 HBUINT16 deltaFormat; /* Format of DeltaValue array data: 1, 2, or 3
3463 * 1 Signed 2-bit value, 8 values per uint16
3464 * 2 Signed 4-bit value, 4 values per uint16
3465 * 3 Signed 8-bit value, 2 values per uint16
3466 */

3468 deltaValueZ; /* Array of compressed data */
3469 public:
3470 DEFINE_SIZE_ARRAY (6, deltaValueZ);
